We recommended the following: 

the Municipal Accountant, Municipal Treasurer and Municipal Mayor see to it that all disbursements are approved or certified by proper officials before any payment of the same are made;


the Head of the Requesting Unit indicate the estimated cost of the goods or services in the Purchase Request as basis of the Municipal Budget Officer of the amount to be obligated; 



Department Heads instruct their subordinates to affix the same signature in all their documents and same be likewise advised to suppliers and contractors;



the Municipal Treasurer direct the Disbursing/Releasing Officer to require signature of payees on the disbursement voucher/payroll before release of payment and to demand authorization of person receiving other than the stated payee.; and


the official or employee who undertook the travel sign Appendix A of the Itinerary of Travel using the prescribed form.

We recommended that Management:


enjoin all officials and employees to strictly comply with the liquidation of cash advances within the prescribed period and ensure that all cash advances granted during the year be liquidated also on the same year;






demand immediate liquidation of the overdue cash advances by sending Demand Letters to concerned Accountable Officers;

We recommended that the Municipal Treasurer:

enjoin the collectors to collect all taxes, fees, charges and revenues from other sources as identified in the Revenue Code;



set realistic targets or goals which are reasonable with the adoption of more strategies to further enhance collections.

We have recommended that the:
a. Municipal Treasurer who is the acting General Service Officer of the Municipality, perform thorough year-end physical count of PPE and prepare Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RCPPE) to be submitted to the Audit Team in accordance with Section 38, Chapter 10, Volume I, of the Government Auditing Manual (GAM);

b. Municipal Accountant properly record and drop from the books all unserviceable PPEs identified in the year-end Report on the Physical Count of PPE in accordance with IPSAS.
